.TH MMIXASM 1 "May 2025" "checksmix 0.2.23"
.SH NAME
mmixasm \- assemble MMIX source into MMO object code
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mmixasm
.RI [ options ]
.RI input.mms
.RI [ input.mms ... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mmixasm
assembles MMIX assembly source
.RB ( .mms )
into an MMO object file. Multiple input files are loaded into one shared
symbol space, as if their contents were concatenated.
.PP
On success it writes the object bytes to the chosen file. During
assembly it prints labels and encoded instructions to standard error to
help with debugging.
.PP
.B Options:
.TP
.BR \-o , \ \-\-output \ \fIOUTPUT.mmo\fR
Write the object file to the specified path. If not provided, the first
input's basename is used with a
.B .mmo
extension.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RUST_LOG
Enable parser and encoder debug logs. Example:
.BR RUST_LOG=checksmix=debug .
.SH EXAMPLES
Assemble and write next to the source:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mmixasm examples/hello_world.mms
.fi
.RE
.PP
Assemble to a specific path, then execute with
.BR checksmix :
.PP
.RS
.nf
mmixasm examples/linked_list.mms -o /tmp/list.mmo
checksmix /tmp/list.mmo
.fi
.RE
.PP
Assemble multiple source files into one shared symbol space:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mmixasm module1.mms module2.mms -o combined.mmo
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR checksmix (1)
